{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"931a","heading":"Art. 131a. Subornation of perjury","label":"931a Art. 131a. Subornation of perjury","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptII/ch47/schX","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective on , as designated by the President, with implementing regulations and provisions relating to applicability to various situations, see and Ex. Ord. No. 13825, set out as notes under .Jan. 1, 2019section 5542 of Pub. L. 114–328section 801 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to take an oath; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to falsely testify, depose, or state upon such oath;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Conditions","label":"b .—Conditions","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The oath is administered with respect to a matter for which such oath is required or authorized by law.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The oath is administered by a person having authority to do so.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Upon the oath, the other person willfully makes or subscribes a statement.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The statement is material.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The statement is false.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s931a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs931a%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"When the statement is made or subscribed, the person subject to this chapter and the other person do not believe that the statement is true.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
